[{"id":"FT542244","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"For&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"0 is less than or equal to theta comma theta is less than or equal to 3 pi over 2\"><math> <mrow> <mn>0</mn> <mo>≤</mo> <mi>θ</mi> <mo>≤</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>3</mn> <mi>π</mi> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac> </mrow> </math></span>, find the greatest distance from any point on the graph of <em>r</em> to the origin. Justify your answer.","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"text-center\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a polar curve in the first and fourth quadrants. The horizontal axis is labeled x, the vertical axis is labeled y, and the origin is labeled O. The vertical axis has 2 tickmarks above and 1 tickmark below the origin. The horizontal axis has 3 tickmarks to the right of the origin. The tickmarks immediately above and to the right of the origin are labeled 1.  The polar curve consists of two loops, a smaller loop inside of a larger loop. The smaller loop is in the first quadrant and has a point at the origin. The larger loop is in the first and fourth quadrants, has a point at the origin, and crosses the x-axis a little beyond x equals 3.\" height=\"214\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/e91b5ef39f4347ef526d66894554df81/original.png\" width=\"200\" /></p>\n\n<p>Consider the polar curve defined by the function&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"r of theta is equal to theta cosine theta\"><math> <mrow> <mi>r</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>θ</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mi>θ</mi> <mi>cos</mi> <mi>θ</mi> </mrow> </math></span>, where&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"0 is less than or equal to theta comma theta is less than or equal to 3 pi over 2\"><math> <mrow> <mn>0</mn> <mo>≤</mo> <mi>θ</mi> <mo>≤</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>3</mn> <mi>π</mi> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac> </mrow> </math></span>. The derivative of the <em>r</em> is given by&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"d r over d theta is equal to cosine theta minus theta sine theta\"><math> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mi>d</mi> <mi>r</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mi>d</mi> <mi>θ</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mi>cos</mi> <mi>θ</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mi>θ</mi> <mi>sin</mi> <mi>θ</mi> </mrow> </math></span>. The figure above shows the graph of <em>r</em> for&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"0 is less than or equal to theta comma theta is less than or equal to 3 pi over 2\"><math> <mrow> <mn>0</mn> <mo>≤</mo> <mi>θ</mi> <mo>≤</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>3</mn> <mi>π</mi> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac> </mrow> </math></span>.</p>\n"}]}]